  <!-- Tiempo recomendado -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="recommended-time-titulo"/></title>
    <p>15 minutos</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[++++++++++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this activity is for students to count their collection in a way that makes sense to them and share how they counted with a partner. Sharing how many objects are in the collection and how they counted will be useful when students represent their count in the next lesson. Most students should be given collections with 6–10 objects. Based on formative assessment data collected in previous sections, adjust the number of objects in collections for individual students. Students are provided with counting mats and 5-frames to help them accurately count or organize their collections. Students use appropriate tools strategically as they choose which tools help them count their collections (MP5).</p>
    <p>Additional collections can be provided to allow students to choose a new collection to count.</p>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Materiales requeridos de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="materials-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <!-- si hay materiales, crear el siguiente archivo -mat.ptx y ponerlos ahí (y agregar también el archivo en la lista de materiales de la lección)-->
    <xi:include href="./act-contemosColecciones-comparteConteo-mat.ptx"/> 
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Launch -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="launch-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Groups of 2</li>
      <li>
        <q>Hoy van a contar otra colección de objetos</q>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Instrucciones para el desarrollo de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="instructions-teacher-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Give each student a bag of objects. Give students access to 5-frames and a counting mat.</li>
      <li>
        <q>Descubran cuántos objetos hay en su colección</q>
      </li>
      <li>2 minutes: independent work time</li>
      <li>
        <q>Cuéntenle a su compañero cuántos objetos hay en su colección. Muéstrenle cómo contaron los objetos</q>
      </li>
      <li>30 seconds: quiet think time</li>
      <li>2 minutes: partner discussion</li>
      <li>Monitor for students who demonstrate how they used a counting mat or 5-frame to count their objects.</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

</prelude>


